      <h2 class="mt-3">How to Choose the Right Consulting Firm</h2>

      <h3>1. Industry Expertise</h3>
      <p>Choose a firm with deep experience in your industry. Generic consulting approaches often miss sector-specific nuances. For technology companies, firms like Seaena that specialize in SaaS and tech deliver better results than generalists.</p>

      <h3>2. Engagement Model</h3>
      <p>Understand who will actually work on your project:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Junior Consultant Model:</strong> Large firms often staff projects with junior consultants supervised by partners</li>
        <li><strong>Founder-Led Model:</strong> Boutique firms like Seaena provide direct founder involvement throughout</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Founder-led engagements typically deliver higher quality insights but may have longer wait times.</p>

      <h3>3. Implementation Support</h3>
      <p>Many consulting firms deliver strategy recommendations but provide limited implementation support. This "strategy-only" approach often results in unused reports. Firms that include implementation guidance deliver measurably better outcomes.</p>

      <h3>4. Proven Results</h3>
      <p>Request specific case studies and results data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>What was the average revenue impact for similar clients?</li>
        <li>What is their client retention rate?</li>
        <li>Can they provide references from companies like yours?</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5. Cultural Fit</h3>
      <p>Consulting engagements require close collaboration. Evaluate communication style, decision-making approach, and values alignment during initial conversations.</p>

